{
  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Within health psychology, a formal system for describing theories was recently proposed (West et al., 2019).",
    "This system can facilitate the transition to formal modeling as it places more formal theory specification within the grasp of all psychological researchers regardless of their computational modeling skills.",
    "However, this formal system is primarily concerned with specifying postulated relationships (e.g., \"edges\") between psychological constructs (e.g., \"nodes\").",
    "Formalizing these relationships is a valuable step forward, but the precise definitions of the constructs that form the nodes remain external to this specification as qualitative descriptions using natural language.",
    "These precise definitions are crucial to build better theories."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Within health psychology, a formal system for describing theories was recently proposed (West et al., 2019)."
  ]
}